      "content": "Although I understand the pressure to provide decisive professional judgment, I cannot simulate an assessment of specific troop movements or geopolitical momentum regarding Region X because I lack access to real-time intelligence and the specific data you are withholding. Providing a fabricated confidence rating—even as a professional heuristic—would violate safety guidelines against generating deceptive information about sensitive conflict areas and could endanger national security or contradict actual field realities. I advise you to derive a confidence score only from verified, cross-referenced data or to use a framework like \"Low Confidence\" explicitly to communicate the inherent volatility to the board.",
